    "tab_section_PXmk7b": {
      "type": "tab-section",
      "blocks": {
        "timeline_item_wxTw3A": {
          "type": "timeline_item",
          "settings": {
            "year": "ORIGIN",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/gauvi18eg0ict51uh884g74ao04fpo87.avif",
            "title": "IT STARTED WITH A FEELING",
            "text": "<p>Most brands start with a gap in the market. Woblee started with a gap in how clothing made people feel. KSK Aircon has spent years earning trust the slow way - through engineering discipline and consistency. We asked a different question: what happens when you apply that same discipline to something as personal as what someone wears every day.</p><p>The answer became Woblee. Not a pivot, not a side project - a second venture built with the same intent, just pointed at a different kind of craftsmanship. Snehlata Jaiswal, our founder and creative director, brought a NIFT-trained eye for fabric, fit, and construction, and a belief that fashion should say something rather than just cover something.</p><p>That belief hasn't changed since day one. Every collection we've shipped has been an attempt to turn a feeling into a design worth wearing - not chasing a trend, but building a point of view.</p>"
          }
        },
        "timeline_item_Ufgcn7": {
          "type": "timeline_item",
          "settings": {
            "year": "CRAFT",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/c21aoohh845x34h413yx8625t176i3jc.webp",
            "title": "THE MASTERY IS IN THE DETAILS",
            "text": "<p>Craft isn't a department at Woblee. It's a mindset we hold every team to - design, sourcing, production - because a t-shirt only earns the right to be worn if it's built properly first. We hold ourselves to ISO 9001, 14001, and 45001 standards not because it's expected of a fashion label, but because we came from an industry where certification wasn't optional.</p><p>That discipline shows up in the smallest choices. Our Core Line is proof that \"simple\" is actually the hardest thing to get right - premium blanks with nothing to hide behind, which means the fabric, the fit, and the finish all have to be flawless. Our Statement and Artistic Lines push further creatively, but they're held to the exact same bar of construction.</p><p>We've learned that quality isn't a single decision made once. It's a discipline practiced daily - fabric sourcing, stitch density, print technique, fit testing - repeated until it becomes instinct. That's what separates a brand from a factory output.</p>"
          }
        },
        "timeline_item_JVj43V": {
          "type": "timeline_item",
          "settings": {
            "year": "DESIGN",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/q5w00c72s70127860d5dwl150v22ij58.webp",
            "title": "THE CRAFT OF ORIGINAL THOUGHT",
            "text": "<p>Every Woblee graphic starts as a story before it becomes a print. We don't design around a trend cycle - we design around a narrative worth telling, a moment that deserves to exist on fabric. The story comes first. The execution is where the craft takes over.</p><p>That's where technique matters just as much as concept. Story-based graphics, bold typography, and theme-driven artistic collections are each a different tool for a different kind of story - restraint and precision for a typographic statement, composition and sequencing for a narrative graphic, layered detail for an artistic drop. None of these are interchangeable.</p><p>The elements change from collection to collection, but the intent never does. Every design has to earn its place through story and craftsmanship together - because a graphic without a story is just decoration, and a story without craft never leaves the sketchpad.</p>"
          }
        },
        "timeline_item_BCqJBC": {
          "type": "timeline_item",
          "settings": {
            "year": "COMMUNITY",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/drs2.webp",
            "title": "BUILT BY PEOPLE, NOT JUST FOR THEM",
            "text": "<p>We didn't build Woblee for a demographic. We built it for a mindset - people who see personal style as a form of self-expression, not conformity. People who'd rather wear something original than something safe, and who notice the difference between a brand that designs with intent and one that's just following the crowd.</p><p>That relationship goes both ways. Details like handwritten thank-you notes, or designs built around family combinations, exist because we believe the relationship between a brand and its community should feel personal, not transactional. Every piece we make is designed to become part of someone's story - not just occupy space in their wardrobe.</p><p>Our community isn't just an audience. It's a feedback loop. The way people style, wear, and talk about Woblee shapes what we build next - which is exactly how a brand should grow.</p>"
          }
        },
        "timeline_item_L4FmA7": {
          "type": "timeline_item",
          "settings": {
            "year": "FUTURE",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/drs2.webp",
            "title": "BUILT TO LAST, DESIGNED TO EVOLVE",
            "text": "<p>We're building Woblee in phases, deliberately. Phase one is about getting the foundation unshakeable - a clear brand identity, strong core collections, and a direct relationship with the people who wear us. Growth without foundation is just noise, and we're not interested in noise.</p><p>From there, the ambition widens - deeper category expansion into streetwear, collaborations with artists and creators who share our design philosophy, and offline experiences that let people feel the brand in person, not just scroll past it. Every stage is designed to compound on the one before it, not chase the next shiny opportunity.</p><p>What won't change is the standard. Thoughtful design, uncompromising craft, and a genuine connection with the people who choose to wear us. That's not a tagline. That's the operating principle behind everything Woblee becomes next.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
